{% extends '_base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}submissions queue{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <h1>
        Submissions queue
    </h1>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md">
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Status</th>
                    <th>Count</th>
                </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                {% for status, count in statistics %}
                    <tr>
                        <td>{{ status.label }}</td>
                        <td>{{ count }}</td>
                    </tr>
                {% endfor %}
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <ul>
                <li><em>{{ constant('App\\Data\\Submission\\Status::NEW').label }}</em> - submissions before initial verification.</li>
                <li><em>{{ constant('App\\Data\\Submission\\Status::IN_REVIEW').label }}</em> - submission after the initial verification, available to the reviewers.</li>
                <li><em>{{ constant('App\\Data\\Submission\\Status::AWAITING_RESPONSE').label }}</em> - an email has been sent to the maker, and there was no response yet.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md">
            <img alt="Number of studios/makers added per month, showing none added in 2026." src="{{ asset('images/creators_added_per_month.png') }}" class="img-fluid">
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-3">Help needed! Looking for reviewers</h2>

    <p>getfursu.it is looking for volunteers for a community-driven reviews process. Wanna help shape getfursu.it data set? Want to give a little of your time to the Community? Join the experiment.</p>

    <h4>What does a reviewer do?</h4>

    <ul>
        <li>Reads the submissions in the <em>{{ constant('App\\Data\\Submission\\Status::NEW').label }}</em> status. Checks the provided information, links.</li>
        <li>
            Tries to answer the questions:
            <ul>
                <li>Should this studio be listed on getfursu.it?</li>
                <li>If yes, does it need to improve the provided information, links? How?</li>
                <li>If not, why? What valuable feedback can we send in response?</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Shares any feedback and concerns with other participants of the review process.</li>
        <li>Upvotes/downvotes other reviewers' feedback. Responds, discusses.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>What tools does a reviewer have?</h4>

    <ul>
        <li>Unfortunately, there is not much now. Partially because this is an experiment, I have no clue how it goes and how much time it's worth investing in development.</li>
        <li>There is a very simple reviews system allowing discussing the submissions and upvoting/downvoting others' posts.</li>
        <li>This system may be improved depending on the outcomes of the experiment, and the reviewers' feedback/requests.</li>
        <li>We could use FursuitReview's Discord server for instant messaging (<a href="{{ path('rt_contact') }}">link on the contact page</a>).</li>
        <li>There are the <a href="{{ path('rt_guidelines') }}">(old) guidelines</a>.</li>
        <li>I'm trying to rewrite the guidelines into instructions for reviewers, <a href="https://github.com/veelkoov/fuzzrake/blob/GUIDELINES-improvements/docs/REVIEWS.md">here (link may change)</a>. This is the-most-work-in-progress part here, I believe. Your feedback, as a reviewer, will help shape this.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>How much time does a reviewer need to spend on reviews?</h4>

    <p>There is no commitment. Hey, a few minutes weekly is more help, than I have now.</p>

    <h4>Who can be a reviewer?</h4>

    <p>Anyone who wants to spend some time helping. Respect for other people is required, as well as the common sense.</p>

    <h4>Have questions?</h4>

    <p>Ask them through the <a href="{{ path('rt_contact') }}">email or social media</a>. You can also <a href="{{ path('rt_feedback_form') }}">submit anonymous feedback</a> (e.g. "I think you should explain this and that").</p>

    <h4>Wanna join the experiment?</h4>

    <p>Please <a href="{{ path('rt_contact') }}">contact me</a> (email is preferred, since I need your address anyway to create an account for you) - "<span class="user-select-all">I want to take part in the getfursu.it reviews experiment</span>". Feel free to add links to some of your social accounts if you have any.</p>

    <h2>See also</h2>

    <p>
        <a href="https://www.tumblr.com/getfursuit/807379325214162944">Tumblr post explaining the situation.</a>
    </p>
{% endblock %}
